

Login into the AWS console 

Choose EC2 in the service. 

In the left menu go to key pair

Click on create key pair

Enter the key pair name as any, in file format change to  .ppk and save it. The ppk file will be downloaded

Click on launch instances

Select  AMI machine Ist one
Click on next, configure instance details

In step 3: configure instance details, in subnet column choose any one of the subnet in the dropdown menu

Then cick next add storage

Then click next add tags

Then click next configure security group

In step 6: configure security group, click add rule, add type HTTP in source change the custom as anywhere (choose in the drop down menu) for both SSH and HTTP

Click review and launch

Choose the existing key pair, as you save before 

click on launch instances

Look on the availability Zone for current running instances

Choose target groups in the side menu

In the target group choose the instance, enter the target group name as any

Click on next, choose the instance 

Click include as pending below

Then click on create target group
Choose load balancer in the side menu

Click Create a load balancer
Choose application load balancer, click create

Type the load balancer name as any
Choose the minimum 2 availability zone(one as same as instance zone)
In listeners and routing, choose the target group that you have created now

Then click on  create a load balancer
The load balancer is created successfully


Open the putty:
In Ubuntu to open putty:(commands)
Ctrl +alt+t  
sudo apt install putty-tools
Putty
Copy the Public IPV4 address for the currently running instance

Then open the putty and enter the Public IPV4 address of the currently created instance

In the left menu click SSH, choose Auth, browse the saved file(.ppk) in downloads and click open.

The terminal is open enter accept in pop up

Then enter the command in terminal  ec2-user

Commands in putty:
        
sudo su
yum install httpd (give yes if asks)
sudo systemctl enable httpd
sudo systemctl start httpd
cd /var/www/html
vim index.html
  Click the Insert icon on the keyboard
  Go to this link copy  the html code(https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html-course-first-web-page-printing-hello-world/)
 Right-click in the terminal and paste the html code.
 Enter escape after that enter:wq
Go to security in the left menu, create a security group in that for inbound key type as HTTP and source type as anywhere IPV4 and outbound key as all traffic and destination type as anywhere IPV4
Go to the instance, right-click and go to  security, in that choose change security groups
Inside change security groups, in the associated security group, remove the already attached security group.
In the search bar, search for the security group that you have created now and click on add security group
Then click Save.
Then open the public IPV4 DNS in the browser, the html file loaded was displayed




